    <title>Layoff Prevention Extension Act of 2015</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-10-03T19:07:25Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2015-07-30</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Layoff Prevention Extension Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Middle Class Tax Relief and Job Creation Act of 2012 with respect to state short-time compensation programs that allow employers to reduce the workweek of their employees in lieu of layoffs. The bill: (1) extends federal financing of the programs for an additional two years; and (2) extends through December 31, 2016, the deadline for a state to submit to the Department of Labor its application for a short-time compensation program grant.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <updateDate>2015-07-30T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
